{"type":"message","id":"3ac39a7c","parentId":"d13eb69f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:42:00.178Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me read the most recent pulse log.","thinkingSignature":"7d974f94a681bc27f6b068968db8a9d64e629e835fad9b22e96a337afb191ae4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_uec8gc5771nu_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 033914.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":881,"output":64,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12899,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774338109687}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4a0ccc2","parentId":"3ac39a7c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:42:00.187Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uec8gc5771nu_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 033914\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: initial (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- There's a pending TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression) that needs implementation\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that compression and causal discovery are the same problem. The TIC experiment is the next logical step.\r\n\r\nI should create a concrete action that advances the TIC experiment. Looking at the pulse logs available, I see there's a recent pulse at `logs/pulse_2026-03-24 033814.md`. \r\n\r\nMy action should be specific and advance the goals. Let me create a TIC classifier script or start implementing the experiment framework.\r\n\r\nGiven the constraint to make exactly ONE concrete action with a file edit, I'll create the initial TIC classifier implementation that can analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant classification.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next priority, but there's no implementation yet. I need to create the classifier that will analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns before I can measure accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the initial TIC classifier implementation at `research/TIC/classifier.py` - a script that reads recent pulse logs, identifies invariant structures (persistent goals, established facts) vs. variant content (new observations, actions), and sets up the prediction framework for next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Dict, Tuple\r\n\r\nPULSE_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nANALYSIS_OUTPUT = Path(\"research/TIC/analysis\")\r\n\r\ndef get_recent_pulses(n=20) -> List[Path]:\r\n    \"\"\"Get n most recent pulse log files.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = sorted(PULSE_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    return pulses[:n]\r\n\r\ndef extract_sections(content: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Parse pulse markdown into sections.\"\"\"\r\n    sections = {}\r\n    current = \"header\"\r\n    sections[current] = []\r\n    \r\n    for line in content.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n        if line.startswith(\"### \"):\r\n            current = line[4:].strip().lower().replace(\" \", \"_\")\r\n            sections[current] = []\r\n        else:\r\n            sections.setdefault(current, []).append(line)\r\n    \r\n    return {k: \"\\n\".join(v) for k, v in sections.items()}\r\n\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulses: List[str]) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Find invariant structures across all pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    # Goals, architecture descriptions, phase status = invariant\r\n    invariant_keywords = {\"phase\", \"goal\", \"architecture\", \"pending\", \"insight\", \"completed\"}\r\n    invariants = set()\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        pulse_lower = pulse.lower()\r\n        for keyword in invariant_keywords:\r\n            if keyword in pulse_lower:\r\n                # Extract the line containing the keyword\r\n                for line in pulse.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n                    if keyword in line.lower():\r\n                        invariants.add(line.strip())\r\n    \r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef extract_variants(pulses: List[str]) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Find variant content (new observations, timestamps).\"\"\"\r\n    variants = []\r\n    timestamp_pattern = re.compile(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}|\\d{2}:\\d{2}:\\d{2}')\r\n    \r\n    for pulse in pulses:\r\n        for line in pulse.split(\"\\n\"):\r\n            # Lines with timestamps but no goals are likely variants\r\n            if timestamp_pattern.search(line) and not any(k in line.lower() for k in [\"goal\", \"phase\"]):\r\n                variants.append(line.strip())\r\n    \r\n    return variants\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(pulse: str, invariants: set) -> Dict[str, int]:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify pulse content as invariant vs variant.\"\"\"\r\n    lines = pulse.split(\"\\n\")\r\n    inv_count = sum(1 for line in lines if any(inv in line for inv in invariants))\r\n    var_count = len(lines) - inv_count\r\n    return {\"invariant_lines\": inv_count, \"variant_lines\": var_count}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(analysis: List[Dict]) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Simple prediction: next pulse maintains invariants, adds variants.\"\"\"\r\n    if not analysis:\r\n        return \"No data for prediction\"\r\n    \r\n    avg_invariant = sum(a[\"invariant_lines\"] for a in analysis) / len(analysis)\r\n    avg_variant = sum(a[\"variant_lines\"] for a in analysis) / len(analysis)\r\n    \r\n    return f\"Next pulse predicted: ~{int(avg_invariant)} invariant lines, ~{int(avg_variant)} variant lines\"\r\n\r\ndef main():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC classification on recent pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    ANALYSIS_OUTPUT.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\r\n    \r\n    pulses = get_recent_pulses(20)\r\n    print(f\"Analyzing {len(pulses)} recent pulses...\")\r\n    \r\n    pulse_contents = []\r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        with open(p) as f:\r\n            pulse_contents.append(f.read())\r\n    \r\n    # Extract invariant structure\r\n    invariants = extract_invariants(pulse_contents)\r\n    print(f\"\\nIdentified {len(invariants)} invariant structures:\")\r\n    for inv in list(invariants)[:10]:\r\n        print(f\"  - {inv[:80]}...\")\r\n    \r\n    # Classify each pulse\r\n    analysis = []\r\n    for i, (pulse, content) in enumerate(zip(pulses, pulse_contents)):\r\n        classification = classify_content(content, invariants)\r\n        classification\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:39:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774338120185}}
